        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 4:38PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Temple, or 8 miles
southeast of Buchanan, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dallas, Buchanan, Villa Rica, Bremen, Temple, Rockmart, Hiram, Waco,
Braswell, Yorkville, Eubank Lake, Van Wert, Abilene, Draketown, and
New Georgia.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
